                <h1>Understanding Counselors' Middle-Class Roots</h1>
                <p>Many counselors come from middle-class backgrounds, shaping their understanding of prevalent societal challenges. They connect with clients on shared experiences and values, allowing for empathetic communication. This common ground fosters trust and makes counseling more effective, as clients feel understood and supported in their unique journeys.</p>
